gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Suns 124, Pelicans 111
gameRecap.excerpt: The Suns defeated the Pelicans, 124-111. Devin Booker led the Suns with 52 points, a career-high eight 3PM, and nine assists, while Kevin Durant (20 points, seven rebounds) and Jusuf Nurkic (19 points, 19 rebounds) combined for 39 points in the victory. Zion Williamson tallied 30 points and five assists for the Pelicans in the losing effort. The Suns improve to 44-31, while the Pelicans fall to 45-30.
